-- East Africa Telecoms Cable May Take Further 15-20 Days to Repair
-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 2012-02-29T14:34:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-29/east-africa-telecoms-cable-may-take-further-15-20-days-to-repair.html
The East African Submarine System, a
telecommunications cable known as EASSy, will take a further 15
to 20 days to repair after it was accidentally cut by a ship on
Feb. 17, the group that owns the cable said on its website
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  